SIMPLE: masonry
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Masonry
<hw>Ma"son*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>ma⟦cced⟧onnerie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The art or
occupation of a mason.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The work or performance of a mason; <as>as, good or
bad <ex>masonry</ex>; skillful <ex>masonry</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That which is built by a mason; anything constructed
of the materials used by masons, such as stone, brick, tiles, or the
like. <stype>Dry masonry</stype> is applied to structures made without
mortar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The craft, institution, or mysteries of Freemasons;
freemasonry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Masoola boat</ent>⟦br⟧
